decks.notes: The deck is focused on aggressive gameplay through a combination of efficient creatures, removal spells, and disruptive cards. Teval, the Balanced Scale, leads the deck and provides powerful abilities to support the aggressive strategy. The deck includes various mana ramp cards like Birds of Paradise and Utopia Sprawl to quickly build up mana and cast threats ahead of curve. Additionally, the deck features a mix of creatures with disruptive abilities like Deathrite Shaman and Endurance, as well as removal spells like Abrupt Decay and Dismember to deal with opposing threats. Overall, the key concept of the deck is to maintain aggression, disrupt the opponent's game plan, and close out the game quickly.

The main goal of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures and burn spells to quickly reduce their life total to zero. With Hazoret the Fervent as the commander, the deck includes a variety of low-cost creatures like Monastery Swiftspear, Goblin Guide, and Soul-Scar Mage, along with powerful burn spells such as Lightning Bolt, Chain Lightning, and Searing Blood. The deck also includes cards like Blood Moon and Magus of the Moon to disrupt opponents' mana bases. By applying early pressure with creatures and finishing with burn spells, this deck aims to end the game as quickly as possible before the opponent can stabilize and mount a comeback.
